name: Turn computer monitors OFF when not in use

measure.comment: Turn computer monitors completely OFF at their power switch or button when not in use. This will save energy even if they already enter a sleep, hibernate, or standby mode once they've remained inactive for a period of time. Consider attaching a small reminder (such as a sticker) to each monitor to remind the user to turn it off when they leave.
measure.name: Turn computer monitors OFF when not in use

name: Add reminders to turn off lights

measure.comment: Add reminders (such as stickers, posters, or wall-plate covers) which remind the last person in the room to turn OFF the lights when they leave the room, even if for just a few minutes.
measure.name: Add reminders to turn off lights

name: Unplug appliance and charger power supplies when not in use

measure.comment: Unplug appliance and charger power supplies when they are not needed such as phone chargers, laptop power supplies, battery charging stations, and other equipment with power adapter 'bricks' which convert AC electricity from the wall to DC electricity for use by the device.
measure.name: Unplug appliance and charger power supplies when not in use

measure.comment: Remove lamps from light fixtures to eliminate over-lighting of the space. Measure light levels before and after removal of lamps to ensure minimum required light levels are still provided. De-lamping may also require re-positioning of some fixture reflectors and other fixture components to ensure proper and equal distribution of light

ecm.name: custom
ecm.description: Delamp to meet minimum foot-candles required

measure.name: Delamp Light Fixtures

name: Lower window shades when air-conditioning is on

measure.comment: Lower any available window shades if the air conditioning is running while solar heat gain is coming in through the windows. This will reduce the cooling load the air conditioning system must satisfy and reduce cooling electricity consumption
measure.name: Lower window shades when air-conditioning is on

name: Manually adjust thermostat within allowable range

measure.comment: Commercial or public space thermostats often have limits on how cool or how warm the set point may be set by an occupant. This said, take advantage of any allowable range of adjustment that is available. If it is cool outside, set the thermostat down a couple degrees. If it's hot outside, set the thermostat up a couple degrees. If it's just right outside, turn the HVAC system off and open the windows (but remember to close them later!).
measure.name: Manually adjust thermostat within allowable range

name: Prohibit use of electric space heaters.

measure.comment: Before using electric space heaters, first work with HVAC technician or controls technician to ensure the HVAC system is doing all that it can to keep the space comfortable. Electric space heaters should be an absolute last resort!
measure.name: Prohibit use of electric space heaters.

name: Turn of lights nearest windows when bright outside

measure.comment: If the row of lights nearest to windows can be individually controlled, turn them off when there is adequate daylight. Measure light levels to ensure minimum standards are still maintained.
measure.name: Turn of lights nearest windows when bright outside
